  "prompt": "I lost my prescription slip for norco 10-325 before having filled it what can I do?",
  "response": "If you've lost your prescription slip for Norco (a combination of hydrocodone and acetaminophen), here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. **Contact Your Prescribing Doctor**: Reach out to the healthcare provider who prescribed the medication. They may be able to provide you with a new prescription or guide you on what to do next.\n\n2. **Request a Refill**: If you have a previous prescription that is still valid and has refills available, you can ask your pharmacy to refill it. They may be able to look it up in their system.\n\n3. **Pharmacy Contact**: If you had previously filled prescriptions with that pharmacy, you can contact them to see if they have a record of your prescription.\n\n4. **Consider Alternative Pain Management**: If you are unable to obtain a new prescription immediately, consider discussing temporary alternatives with your healthcare provider.\n\n5. **Keep Documentation**: If you get a new prescription, keep the documentation in a safe place to avoid future losses.\n\nMake sure to follow all legal regulations regarding controlled substances, as Norco is classified as a Schedule II drug, which means it has strict prescribing and dispensing rules.",
